.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE SLOPPY-JOES M "11 Jul 86" 1986
.RZ "MA FOSTER'S SLOPPY JOES" "A spicy and simple sloppy joe"
This recipe comes from my wife's mom, who got it from her mother-in-law
in western New York state.
It's very easy to make and tastes a lot better than any mix.
.IH "Serves 4"
.IG "1 lb" "ground beef" "500 g"
.IG "1" "onion,"
chopped
.IG "1 cup" "catsup" "250 ml"
.IG "2 Tbsp" "vinegar" "30 ml"
.IG "2 Tbsp" "sugar" "30 ml"
.IG "2 Tbsp" "mustard" "30 ml"
.IG "2 Tbsp" "Worcestershire sauce" "30 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "celery seed" "5 ml"
.IG "" "salt and pepper,"
to taste
.PH
.SK 1
In a frying pan, brown ground beef and onion.
.SK 2
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 15 minutes or more.
.SK 3
Serve hot by scooping the mixture onto toasted buns.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
5 minutes preparation, 15 minutes cooking.
.I Precision:
approximate measurement OK.
.WR
Dennis Wombough 
AT&T Bell Labs Holmdel, New Jersey
